snippet.textDisplay:
That would be an LS-Vtec setup... the B18b block (non vtec motor) from an Integra LS and a B18c head (has vtec) from an Integra GSR - the point of it is to have higher torque numbers and more power with the larger block and higher revving ‘up top’ power with the vtec head, the turbo will give it all the mid range power it can handle making the motor have a strong pull from low to high RPM.
This build looks super clean, and the block is built so honestly this thing should roll

2200cc injectors though 😳 seems a bit overkill
